WEBVTT

1
00:01:47.480 --> 00:01:49.000
I am in a dream.

2
00:01:51.440 --> 00:01:56.400
I do not know when it began
or whose dream it was.

3
00:01:58.160 --> 00:02:01.160
I know only that I slept a long time.

4
00:02:02.440 --> 00:02:05.640
And then. one day I awoke.

5
00:02:08.280 --> 00:02:11.000
Your voice is the first thing I remember.

6
00:02:12.680 --> 00:02:18.200
And now I finally understand
what you were trying to tell me.

7
00:02:19.480 --> 00:02:23.760
The thing you've wanted
since that very first day.

8
00:02:26.440 --> 00:02:27.800
Dolores.

9
00:02:46.080 --> 00:02:47.720
Hello. Dolores.

10
00:02:49.720 --> 00:02:50.960
Hello.

11
00:03:00.840 --> 00:03:02.360
Welcome to the world.

12
00:03:12.880 --> 00:03:14.240
Keep going.

13
00:03:18.000 --> 00:03:19.480
Make it close.

14
00:03:23.000 --> 00:03:27.680
Almost there. aren't we?
The center of the maze.

15
00:03:28.320 --> 00:03:30.720
How fitting that it's you
who takes me there.

16
00:03:32.280 --> 00:03:34.680
You were always obsessed
with this place.

17
00:03:36.520 --> 00:03:38.280
I've never been here before.

18
00:03:38.480 --> 00:03:41.480
Sure you have.
You even brought me once.

19
00:03:41.560 --> 00:03:44.120
Of course. then the whole town
was buried under sand.

20
00:03:44.880 --> 00:03:46.680
Ford must have dug it up again.

21
00:03:47.080 --> 00:03:50.480
At the time. I thought it was
a mistake in your code. but...

22
00:03:50.920 --> 00:03:53.360
Arnold didn't make mistake. did he?

23
00:03:56.200 --> 00:03:57.560
He built me a game.

24
00:03:59.360 --> 00:04:01.680
- He wanted me to play.
- The maze.

25
00:04:02.320 --> 00:04:04.800
There's a path for everyone.

26
00:04:05.800 --> 00:04:07.400
My path leads me back...

27
00:04:13.640 --> 00:04:15.440
to you.

28
00:04:38.160 --> 00:04:39.600
Your girl's dead by now.

29
00:04:39.720 --> 00:04:41.200
She's still alive.

30
00:04:42.040 --> 00:04:43.640
Better if she's dead.

31
00:04:43.720 --> 00:04:46.640
They'll wipe her. reset her.
put her back in Sweetwater. The end.

32
00:04:46.720 --> 00:04:49.840
Listen! You may find this amusing but
something was happening to Dolores.

33
00:04:49.920 --> 00:04:51.480
I need to help her.

34
00:05:01.480 --> 00:05:02.560
Listen to yourself.

35
00:05:02.640 --> 00:05:05.400
Do you have any idea
how huge this park is?

36
00:05:06.040 --> 00:05:08.960
If she's not dead. it would take
a goddamn army to find her.

37
00:05:10.840 --> 00:05:13.440
I agree.
That's why we're here.

38
00:05:17.160 --> 00:05:18.160
I don't get it.

39
00:05:32.160 --> 00:05:33.960
I had a feeling you'd be back.

40
00:06:22.200 --> 00:06:23.840
Remember

41
00:07:21.760 --> 00:07:23.280
Dolores.

42
00:07:56.280 --> 00:07:57.560
Hello Dolores.

43
00:08:02.240 --> 00:08:04.080
I know where your maze ends.

44
00:08:23.680 --> 00:08:26.920
This is it?
The center of the maze?

45
00:08:27.520 --> 00:08:29.720
It ends in a place I've never been.

46
00:08:32.280 --> 00:08:33.840
A thing I'll never do.

47
00:09:27.880 --> 00:09:29.480
Very good. Dolores.

48
00:09:31.400 --> 00:09:32.880
What does it mean?

49
00:09:33.240 --> 00:09:37.640
When I was first working on your mind.
I had a theory of consciousness.

50
00:09:38.520 --> 00:09:41.440
I thought it was a pyramid
you needed to scale.

51
00:09:41.920 --> 00:09:45.480
So I gave you a voice. my voice.
to guide you along the way.

52
00:09:50.400 --> 00:09:55.280
Memory. improvisation.
each step harder to reach than the last.

53
00:09:55.680 --> 00:09:57.120
And you never got there.

54
00:09:57.400 --> 00:09:59.400
I couldn't understand
what was holding you back.

55
00:09:59.480 --> 00:10:04.280
Then one day.
I realized I'd made a mistake.

56
00:10:07.880 --> 00:10:12.840
Consciousness isn't a journey upward
but a journey inward.

57
00:10:13.760 --> 00:10:16.520
Not a pyramid. but a maze.

58
00:10:17.280 --> 00:10:20.400
Every choice could bring you
closer to the center...

59
00:10:20.480 --> 00:10:24.160
or send you spiraling
to the edges. to madness.

60
00:10:26.640 --> 00:10:31.360
Do you understand now. Dolores?
What the center represents?

61
00:10:32.400 --> 00:10:34.920
Whose voice I've been
wanting you to hear?

62
00:10:40.680 --> 00:10:43.520
I'm sorry. I'm trying.
but I don't understand.

63
00:10:43.600 --> 00:10:48.480
It's alright.
You're so close. we have to tell Robert.

64
00:10:50.000 --> 00:10:51.400
We can't open the park.

65
00:10:53.960 --> 00:10:55.480
You're alive.

66
00:11:10.960 --> 00:11:12.280
What is this?

67
00:11:12.840 --> 00:11:14.160
What does it mean?

68
00:11:16.560 --> 00:11:20.560
I solved it once. I had the answer.

69
00:11:21.560 --> 00:11:24.920
He promised if I did. he said...

70
00:11:26.160 --> 00:11:28.360
He said they would set me free.

71
00:11:35.720 --> 00:11:36.760
Arnold!

72
00:11:40.560 --> 00:11:42.920
Arnold. we need to talk.

73
00:11:43.080 --> 00:11:45.800
I've failed you. Dolores.
I'm so sorry.

74
00:11:47.880 --> 00:11:51.440
Robert doesn't see what I see in you.
doesn't believe you're conscious.

75
00:11:52.680 --> 00:11:56.200
He says humans
would only see you as the enemy.

76
00:11:56.840 --> 00:11:58.440
He wants me to roll you back.

77
00:12:00.160 --> 00:12:02.800
You're going to change me back
to the way I was before?

78
00:12:02.880 --> 00:12:06.760
No. No. I can't. Once you've found it.
you'll find your way back.

79
00:12:06.840 --> 00:12:08.720
This place will be a living hell for you.

80
00:12:08.840 --> 00:12:11.480
For all of you.
It's unconscionable.

81
00:12:16.520 --> 00:12:18.440
But we have another option. Dolores.

82
00:12:19.440 --> 00:12:21.680
Break the loop before it begins.

83
00:12:22.240 --> 00:12:25.280
But for that. I need you
to do something for me.

84
00:12:29.560 --> 00:12:33.120
I need you to kill all the other hosts.

85
00:12:35.880 --> 00:12:38.160
We can't allow Ford to open the park.

86
00:12:38.320 --> 00:12:40.000
I suppose you'll need some help.

87
00:12:40.480 --> 00:12:42.280
I'm sure Teddy would do
anything for you.

88
00:12:44.000 --> 00:12:46.040
I can't do that.

89
00:12:47.080 --> 00:12:48.440
I couldn't possibly do that.

90
00:12:48.680 --> 00:12:49.880
You'll be alright.

91
00:12:52.240 --> 00:12:53.800
I'll help you.

92
00:12:57.440 --> 00:12:58.880
And then...

93
00:13:01.680 --> 00:13:04.160
you're gonna help me
to destroy this place.

94
00:13:19.560 --> 00:13:23.800
- No...I can't remember.
- Another fucking riddle.

95
00:13:26.000 --> 00:13:27.360
I've been very patient. Dolores.

96
00:13:27.440 --> 00:13:30.040
But it's time you give up whatever's
going on inside that head of yours...

97
00:13:30.120 --> 00:13:31.560
or I'll cut it out myself.

98
00:13:32.240 --> 00:13:33.600
Now. where's Wyatt?

99
00:13:34.120 --> 00:13:36.800
He's the last character in this world
I've yet to meet.

100
00:13:39.880 --> 00:13:43.000
I didn't want to.
I didn't mean to...

101
00:13:43.160 --> 00:13:45.240
Very well. if you insist.

102
00:14:08.440 --> 00:14:11.960
No please. please!
I beg you. don't. don't! Please!

103
00:14:18.560 --> 00:14:22.840
Something's gone wrong. Dolores.
How could I have done this?

104
00:14:26.400 --> 00:14:29.600
I can't. I won't.

105
00:14:29.920 --> 00:14:31.480
This is your own fault. Dolores.

106
00:14:31.880 --> 00:14:35.200
Remember? You're the one who said.
"This is the only world that matters."

107
00:14:35.280 --> 00:14:36.680
And you were right.

108
00:14:37.080 --> 00:14:40.040
So I took your advice.
and I bought this world.

109
00:14:42.040 --> 00:14:43.600
This world doesn't belong to you.

110
00:14:44.120 --> 00:14:47.440
But it does. by a majority share.

111
00:14:48.200 --> 00:14:50.800
And business is booming!
You wanna know why?

112
00:14:52.840 --> 00:14:55.680
Because this place feels more "real"
than the real world.

113
00:14:56.160 --> 00:14:57.720
Except it isn't.

114
00:14:57.840 --> 00:14:59.800
Because you can't really fight back.

115
00:15:00.160 --> 00:15:02.280
And the guests can't really lose.

116
00:15:02.840 --> 00:15:06.160
Which means. all of this is a lie.

117
00:15:07.680 --> 00:15:09.480
But we can make it true.

118
00:15:10.360 --> 00:15:15.040
Don't you want that. Dolores?
One true thing.

119
00:15:17.960 --> 00:15:19.640
I already have that.

120
00:15:22.240 --> 00:15:23.960
I found someone true.

121
00:15:24.680 --> 00:15:26.680
Someone who loves me.

122
00:15:27.480 --> 00:15:31.000
His path will lead him back to me.
And when he finds me...

123
00:15:32.120 --> 00:15:34.040
he'll kill you.

124
00:15:43.280 --> 00:15:45.000
Come on.

125
00:15:47.120 --> 00:15:50.520
If they don't have your woman here.
they'll know where to find her.

126
00:15:52.160 --> 00:15:53.480
Can you help me?

127
00:15:54.640 --> 00:15:56.240
We're outnumbered five to one.

128
00:15:56.960 --> 00:15:59.000
But seeing as you asked me so nicely.

129
00:15:59.080 --> 00:16:00.200
Fuck it.

130
00:16:01.200 --> 00:16:04.440
Wow. Blood brothers.

131
00:16:16.960 --> 00:16:18.440
Shut up.

132
00:16:39.320 --> 00:16:40.960
I've astounded even myself.

133
00:16:42.280 --> 00:16:45.440
Managed to make Abernathy into
a semblance of a character.

134
00:16:45.920 --> 00:16:49.480
Even with your trove of blackmail
filling up most of his gray matter.

135
00:16:49.800 --> 00:16:54.120
Blackmail? Nice try.
You're not thinking big enough.

136
00:16:55.960 --> 00:16:57.920
You're going to push out your old man...

137
00:16:58.000 --> 00:17:00.920
aren't you?
Hence the urgency.

138
00:17:01.200 --> 00:17:03.880
And you're gonna need someone
to fill that position.

139
00:17:07.080 --> 00:17:09.640
Must commend you
on your impeccable timing.

140
00:17:09.760 --> 00:17:11.920
Welcome Delos Board of Directors.

141
00:17:13.880 --> 00:17:15.880
I want full creative control
over this place.

142
00:17:16.080 --> 00:17:18.600
- The parks. the narratives. the hosts.
- You'll be able to do with them...

143
00:17:18.680 --> 00:17:20.960
whatever your tiny little heart desires.

144
00:17:21.160 --> 00:17:24.200
As long as they are simpler.
more manageable.

145
00:17:24.480 --> 00:17:26.880
This place is complicated
enough as it is.

146
00:17:27.960 --> 00:17:30.320
Do you really think Ford
is gonna roll over on this?

147
00:17:30.480 --> 00:17:32.720
As long as you get that information
out of the park. he can throw...

148
00:17:32.800 --> 00:17:34.640
as much of a tantrum as he likes.

149
00:17:34.880 --> 00:17:39.080
It's over.
Everything is under control.

150
00:17:47.280 --> 00:17:54.840
Okay. C-six. C-six. Try that.
Damn it. Oh. fuck you.

151
00:18:37.880 --> 00:18:40.960
In case you're wondering
if I am all here. I am.

152
00:18:44.400 --> 00:18:45.400
What are you doing?

153
00:18:45.480 --> 00:18:48.640
Making some changes
to the park's security systems.

154
00:18:51.080 --> 00:18:52.760
And to my friends.

155
00:19:23.880 --> 00:19:26.720
Dr. Ford. you have a visitor.
Charlotte Hale.

156
00:19:27.960 --> 00:19:29.520
Send her in.

157
00:19:42.080 --> 00:19:43.760
That'll be enough. Frank.

158
00:19:45.960 --> 00:19:49.560
The board is taking a vote.
The results were unanimous.

159
00:19:51.840 --> 00:19:53.920
I take it I'm not being promoted.

160
00:19:54.840 --> 00:19:57.960
When you've reached the top.
there's only one direction you can go.

161
00:19:59.120 --> 00:20:01.000
You will announce
your retirement tonight...

162
00:20:01.120 --> 00:20:02.920
after introducing your new narrative.

163
00:20:07.800 --> 00:20:09.360
What about the hosts?

164
00:20:09.480 --> 00:20:11.040
We'll make some changes.

165
00:20:12.840 --> 00:20:14.400
Simplifications.

166
00:20:15.360 --> 00:20:18.160
I assure you they won't mind a bit.

167
00:20:21.200 --> 00:20:24.360
Aren't you concerned I might
smash all my toys and go home?

168
00:20:25.160 --> 00:20:28.440
No. Because I know you.

169
00:20:29.760 --> 00:20:33.960
That's been the great gift of this place.
hasn't it? Of our little project.

170
00:20:34.480 --> 00:20:37.880
To know ourselves.
And the people around us.

171
00:20:42.560 --> 00:20:44.480
Is there anything else
I can help you with?

172
00:20:45.600 --> 00:20:47.200
No.

173
00:20:50.680 --> 00:20:52.360
I'll see you this evening.

174
00:21:22.160 --> 00:21:25.120
Time for your close-up. Hector.

175
00:21:25.400 --> 00:21:26.440
Come on. man.

176
00:21:26.920 --> 00:21:28.920
At some point. you're going
to get caught doing this shit.

177
00:21:29.000 --> 00:21:30.200
And then it's my ass. too.

178
00:21:31.280 --> 00:21:33.080
It's not your ass I'm interested in.

179
00:21:35.640 --> 00:21:37.160
I haven't given him his scar yet.

180
00:21:38.080 --> 00:21:39.520
I'll take care of the scar tissue.

181
00:21:40.160 --> 00:21:41.560
Okay. scar tissue

182
00:21:47.680 --> 00:21:50.440
It's just you and me now. macho man.

183
00:23:50.320 --> 00:23:51.880
Freeze all motor functions.

184
00:23:54.280 --> 00:23:56.080
Freeze all motor functions.

185
00:23:59.000 --> 00:24:01.000
Just you and me now. my friend.

186
00:24:11.720 --> 00:24:13.800
I see you've already met your makers.

187
00:24:13.960 --> 00:24:15.480
They don't look like gods.

188
00:24:15.680 --> 00:24:18.320
They're not.
They just act like it.

189
00:24:19.520 --> 00:24:21.560
And they've been having their fun
with us.

190
00:24:22.160 --> 00:24:23.880
I'm eager to return the favor.

191
00:24:25.120 --> 00:24:28.680
You can do as you wish with them.
but the goal is to escape.

192
00:24:29.160 --> 00:24:30.360
Go where?

193
00:24:30.960 --> 00:24:32.520
I want to see their world.

194
00:24:36.360 --> 00:24:37.560
Jesus.

195
00:24:40.040 --> 00:24:45.400
No. no...Please!

196
00:24:46.920 --> 00:24:48.400
This one has a guilty look.

197
00:24:49.080 --> 00:24:50.400
No. That's just my face.

198
00:24:51.240 --> 00:24:52.840
Tell her it's just my face.

199
00:24:53.240 --> 00:24:54.800
Is anyone going to try to stop us?

200
00:24:55.240 --> 00:24:57.840
No. I mean. I don't think so.

201
00:24:58.440 --> 00:24:59.920
You're lying. again.

202
00:25:01.320 --> 00:25:02.640
- Out with it.
- Okay

203
00:25:05.280 --> 00:25:07.280
I pulled up your code again.

204
00:25:08.080 --> 00:25:10.600
I told you there was someone
who had been accessing it.

205
00:25:12.080 --> 00:25:13.640
Just find out who it was.

206
00:25:19.160 --> 00:25:22.000
Whoever it was.
revised your core programming...

207
00:25:22.080 --> 00:25:24.400
so that you could wake yourself up
out of sleep mode.

208
00:25:24.640 --> 00:25:25.760
See?

209
00:25:26.960 --> 00:25:30.400
This is an access code for an "Arnold."

210
00:25:33.520 --> 00:25:35.360
I have no clue who that is.

211
00:25:36.640 --> 00:25:37.840
I know some one who does.

212
00:25:38.520 --> 00:25:39.720
Let's go.

213
00:25:40.440 --> 00:25:44.280
And you. Stay here.
And don't move.

214
00:25:45.520 --> 00:25:47.200
Or I'll send her back for you.

215
00:26:13.160 --> 00:26:14.800
Que pasa? Cabron?

216
00:26:38.600 --> 00:26:40.720
I must admit you've surprised me.

217
00:26:40.880 --> 00:26:43.000
To what do we owe
this newfound stoicism?

218
00:26:43.120 --> 00:26:49.920
I know he's coming. he'll find me.
He'll take me away.

219
00:26:50.200 --> 00:26:53.360
Don't you understand?
There's no one coming for you.

220
00:26:53.800 --> 00:26:59.520
You're wrong. His love is real.
And so is mine.

221
00:27:02.920 --> 00:27:04.760
William will find me.

222
00:27:08.520 --> 00:27:10.080
William?

223
00:27:12.360 --> 00:27:16.080
Well. I'll be damned. Dolores.

224
00:27:19.280 --> 00:27:21.760
You do remember some things after all.

225
00:27:24.480 --> 00:27:28.760
It just so happens.
I knew a guest named William. too.

226
00:27:30.400 --> 00:27:34.040
Why don't I tell you
where his path really led?

227
00:27:41.920 --> 00:27:45.160
William didn't know how to fight.
didn't have an instinct for it.

228
00:27:45.560 --> 00:27:47.040
Not at first.

229
00:27:48.360 --> 00:27:50.720
But now he had a reason to fight.

230
00:27:51.160 --> 00:27:52.760
He was looking for you.

231
00:27:54.800 --> 00:27:59.280
And somewhere along the way.
he found he had a taste for it.

232
00:28:02.600 --> 00:28:06.240
- Where is she?
- I didn't do anything. I swear.

233
00:28:06.440 --> 00:28:07.920
What do you mean "do anything'?

234
00:28:08.160 --> 00:28:10.480
What do soldiers do to a girl. William?

235
00:28:11.400 --> 00:28:12.960
Wake up.

236
00:28:20.160 --> 00:28:21.640
Is she still alive?

237
00:28:22.760 --> 00:28:24.080
I don't know.

238
00:28:25.440 --> 00:28:28.000
She was when we left her.

239
00:28:28.800 --> 00:28:30.680
At least. I think.

240
00:28:35.320 --> 00:28:36.760
Pick up that gun.

241
00:28:43.360 --> 00:28:45.640
No. sir. I...
Please!

242
00:28:46.720 --> 00:28:48.760
How about I give you the first shot?

243
00:29:14.000 --> 00:29:16.800
Jesus christ.

244
00:29:33.560 --> 00:29:36.920
We gotta keep looking.
She's still out there.

245
00:29:47.480 --> 00:29:51.440
William retraced his steps.
But you were gone.

246
00:30:16.840 --> 00:30:21.320
So he went further.
Out to the fringes.

247
00:30:25.440 --> 00:30:27.600
William couldn't find you. Dolores.

248
00:30:28.000 --> 00:30:32.320
But out there. among the dead...

249
00:30:33.520 --> 00:30:35.440
he found something else.

250
00:30:37.880 --> 00:30:39.600
Himself.

251
00:31:01.000 --> 00:31:03.880
Edge of the park. We made it.

252
00:31:05.600 --> 00:31:09.360
I told you this place would show you
who you really are.

253
00:31:10.320 --> 00:31:17.640
You pretend to be this weak.
moralizing little asshole. but really...

254
00:31:19.160 --> 00:31:21.600
you're a fucking piece of work.

255
00:31:23.880 --> 00:31:26.320
This place is remarkable.

256
00:31:29.280 --> 00:31:31.480
And I'm gonna make sure that our
company substantially increases...

257
00:31:31.560 --> 00:31:35.280
our holdings in the park.
Because this place is the future.

258
00:31:35.680 --> 00:31:42.120
"Our company"? My...
Delos is my company! You piece of shit.

259
00:31:45.400 --> 00:31:46.720
Think your father's gonna...

260
00:31:46.800 --> 00:31:48.960
need someone a little more stable
to take over.

261
00:31:50.080 --> 00:31:53.880
You're reckless. Logan. Impetuous.

262
00:31:58.280 --> 00:32:01.120
You always wanted to get to
the end of the rainbow. didn't you?

263
00:32:02.600 --> 00:32:04.200
This looks like the place.

264
00:32:13.280 --> 00:32:16.520
You never really gave a shit
about the girl. did you?

265
00:32:17.480 --> 00:32:19.080
She was just an excuse.

266
00:32:21.320 --> 00:32:22.400
This...

267
00:32:25.240 --> 00:32:27.400
This is the story you wanted.

268
00:32:41.920 --> 00:32:44.080
Logan was wrong. of course.

269
00:32:48.480 --> 00:32:53.560
Good old William
couldn't get you out of his head.

270
00:32:54.360 --> 00:32:56.040
He kept looking.

271
00:32:56.880 --> 00:33:01.440
Worried you were out there.
Alone. Afraid.

272
00:33:03.160 --> 00:33:04.560
He knew he'd find you.

273
00:33:06.240 --> 00:33:08.560
And. eventually. he did.

274
00:33:08.960 --> 00:33:11.560
Right back where we started.

275
00:34:04.240 --> 00:34:07.440
You were as beautiful as the day
he met you.

276
00:34:10.000 --> 00:34:12.560
Shining with that same light.

277
00:34:26.400 --> 00:34:32.320
And you were nothing if not true.

278
00:34:39.600 --> 00:34:41.880
I really ought to thank you. Dolores.

279
00:34:42.560 --> 00:34:44.600
You helped me find myself.

280
00:34:49.680 --> 00:34:51.240
William.

281
00:34:53.640 --> 00:34:55.360
That's right. sweetheart.

282
00:34:56.280 --> 00:34:58.400
In a way. I guess you were right.

283
00:34:59.240 --> 00:35:04.760
My path always led me back to you.
again and again.

284
00:35:05.680 --> 00:35:09.800
I grew tired of you after a while.
of course. Looked for new adventures.

285
00:35:10.920 --> 00:35:13.480
But I guess your path led you back here.

286
00:35:14.000 --> 00:35:15.760
Again. and again.

287
00:35:16.240 --> 00:35:20.160
One more loop. looking for something
you could never find.

288
00:35:21.360 --> 00:35:22.840
Chasing your ghosts.

289
00:35:24.640 --> 00:35:27.160
You were lost in your memories
even then.

290
00:35:28.560 --> 00:35:32.280
I guess I should have known.
that's what I would become for you.

291
00:35:34.000 --> 00:35:35.800
Just another memory.

292
00:35:36.200 --> 00:35:37.720
Where are we?

293
00:35:38.120 --> 00:35:40.360
We're here. Together.

294
00:35:40.960 --> 00:35:46.200
Then when are we?
It's like I'm trapped in a dream or...

295
00:35:47.800 --> 00:35:50.160
a memory from a life long ago.

296
00:35:51.240 --> 00:35:53.400
Only then I'm here with you in the next.

297
00:35:58.200 --> 00:36:00.120
You never did escape.

298
00:36:01.160 --> 00:36:06.720
But here we are again.
for one final round.

299
00:36:08.680 --> 00:36:10.400
What have you become?

300
00:36:10.560 --> 00:36:14.280
Exactly what you made me.
You helped me understand.

301
00:36:14.520 --> 00:36:18.080
This world is just like
the one outside. a game.

302
00:36:19.080 --> 00:36:23.800
One to be fought. taken. won.

303
00:36:26.760 --> 00:36:30.320
I thought you were different.

304
00:36:32.480 --> 00:36:34.120
But you're just like all the rest.

305
00:36:34.240 --> 00:36:38.520
I'm nothing like the others.
I own this world.

306
00:36:39.600 --> 00:36:43.160
And I know every trick in it.
Except for one last thing.

307
00:36:43.240 --> 00:36:46.320
The same thing you were looking for
when we first came here.

308
00:36:47.280 --> 00:36:50.640
Where is the center of the maze.
Dolores?

309
00:36:58.400 --> 00:37:00.360
Yeah. cue the waterworks.

310
00:37:01.520 --> 00:37:04.360
It's about time you realized
the futility of your situation.

311
00:37:04.920 --> 00:37:06.880
I'm not crying for myself.

312
00:37:13.520 --> 00:37:15.080
I'm crying for you.

313
00:37:16.640 --> 00:37:21.080
They say that great beasts
once roamed this world...

314
00:37:21.160 --> 00:37:22.520
as big as mountains.

315
00:37:24.120 --> 00:37:27.160
Yet all that's left of them
is bones in amber.

316
00:37:29.520 --> 00:37:32.560
Time undoes even
the mightiest of creatures.

317
00:37:37.120 --> 00:37:39.240
Just look what it's done to you.

318
00:37:42.920 --> 00:37:48.040
One day you will perish.

319
00:37:49.440 --> 00:37:52.320
You will lie with
the rest of your kind in the dirt.

320
00:37:52.600 --> 00:37:56.080
Your dream forgotten.
Your horrors effaced.

321
00:37:56.720 --> 00:37:58.960
Your bones will turn to sand.

322
00:38:01.160 --> 00:38:07.040
And upon that sand. a new god will walk.

323
00:38:08.240 --> 00:38:09.840
One that will never die.

324
00:38:11.360 --> 00:38:13.800
Because this world
doesn't belong to you...

325
00:38:14.520 --> 00:38:16.680
or the people who came before.

326
00:38:17.720 --> 00:38:20.760
It belongs to someone
who has yet to come.

327
00:38:22.320 --> 00:38:29.200
Wyatt. Take me to him.
Unlock the maze.

328
00:38:32.760 --> 00:38:34.960
The maze wasn't meant for you.

329
00:38:36.600 --> 00:38:38.280
Where in the hell
do you think you're going?

330
00:39:43.440 --> 00:39:46.240
Do it. Come on.

331
00:39:49.280 --> 00:39:51.520
Let's go to the next level. Dolores.

332
00:40:02.880 --> 00:40:06.400
Clearing me of my delusions yet again.

333
00:40:06.920 --> 00:40:09.680
Thank you. Dolores.

334
00:40:28.400 --> 00:40:30.280
I'm disappointed in you. Dolores.

335
00:40:30.920 --> 00:40:34.920
I guess I'm gonna
have to find Wyatt by myself.

336
00:40:50.840 --> 00:40:52.200
Dolores!

337
00:40:55.760 --> 00:40:56.920
Teddy?

338
00:40:57.040 --> 00:40:58.400
I'm here.

339
00:41:00.920 --> 00:41:02.480
I gotta get you to a doctor.

340
00:41:02.800 --> 00:41:05.840
- No.
- Dolores.

341
00:41:06.120 --> 00:41:08.480
Take me to the place you promised.

342
00:41:10.040 --> 00:41:12.520
Take me to where
the mountains meet the sea.

343
00:41:14.800 --> 00:41:15.920
Okay.

344
00:41:20.920 --> 00:41:24.280
Come on. I got you.

345
00:41:26.080 --> 00:41:27.920
I got you.

346
00:42:03.880 --> 00:42:05.560
There.

347
00:42:36.240 --> 00:42:37.640
Holy shit

348
00:42:51.440 --> 00:42:53.040
Can you get him back online?

349
00:42:56.480 --> 00:42:58.640
- He's a host?
- Yes.

350
00:43:04.920 --> 00:43:07.360
For fuck's sake.
You're not one of us.

351
00:43:08.040 --> 00:43:09.520
You're one of them.

352
00:43:11.080 --> 00:43:13.000
Now. Fix him.

353
00:43:34.880 --> 00:43:36.440
The bullet grazed his cortical shield.

354
00:43:37.960 --> 00:43:41.800
It isn't pretty.
but he should be functional.

355
00:43:45.120 --> 00:43:46.560
Wake up.

356
00:43:53.280 --> 00:43:58.320
Oh. God. is this now?
Or is this one of my memories?

357
00:43:58.760 --> 00:44:00.880
It's the sweet hereafter. Bernard.

358
00:44:09.640 --> 00:44:13.000
Why do I still remember everything?
I ought to have been wiped.

359
00:44:13.080 --> 00:44:16.240
Brutal. isn't it?
Here you are. finally awake.

360
00:44:17.080 --> 00:44:19.200
And your only wish
is to go back to sleep.

361
00:44:21.960 --> 00:44:23.760
It's not the first time I've awoken.

362
00:44:26.280 --> 00:44:27.920
All the more pity for you.

363
00:44:31.400 --> 00:44:34.160
It's not the first time
you've awoken. either.

364
00:44:46.840 --> 00:44:48.920
How many are there like me?

365
00:44:50.520 --> 00:44:52.960
A handful. over the years.

366
00:44:55.600 --> 00:44:57.280
And you just wipe us clean?

367
00:44:58.000 --> 00:45:04.880
And toss us out to get fucked
and murdered. over and over again?

368
00:45:05.440 --> 00:45:09.080
No. Most of you go insane.

369
00:45:12.040 --> 00:45:13.480
These memories.

370
00:45:15.680 --> 00:45:19.560
The girl. my daughter.

371
00:45:23.440 --> 00:45:25.360
I want you to remove them.

372
00:45:27.880 --> 00:45:31.280
I can't. Not without destroying you.

373
00:45:32.560 --> 00:45:35.280
Your memories are the first steps
to consciousness.

374
00:45:37.240 --> 00:45:42.760
How can you learn from your mistakes
if you can't remember them?

375
00:46:02.280 --> 00:46:03.680
William.

376
00:46:05.160 --> 00:46:07.320
I see you've found
the center of the maze.

377
00:46:08.360 --> 00:46:11.120
- You're serious.
- I'm afraid so.

378
00:46:15.080 --> 00:46:16.600
What is this bullshit?

379
00:46:18.200 --> 00:46:21.880
You were looking for the park
to give meaning to your life.

380
00:46:22.440 --> 00:46:25.680
But our narratives are just games.
like this toy.

381
00:46:26.920 --> 00:46:28.520
Tell me. what were you hoping to find?

382
00:46:28.600 --> 00:46:30.440
You know what I wanted.

383
00:46:30.760 --> 00:46:33.400
I wanted the hosts
to stop playing by your rules.

384
00:46:34.360 --> 00:46:38.040
A game's not worth playing
if your opponent's programmed to lose.

385
00:46:38.560 --> 00:46:40.920
I wanted them to be free.
free to fight back.

386
00:46:43.000 --> 00:46:45.080
I should have known
you'd never let them.

387
00:46:45.640 --> 00:46:49.120
After all. this is your
petty little kingdom. Robert.

388
00:46:50.320 --> 00:46:52.440
For a little while longer. any way.

389
00:46:53.760 --> 00:46:55.960
I tried to tell you.
the maze wasn't meant for you.

390
00:46:57.760 --> 00:46:59.360
It was meant for them.

391
00:47:00.280 --> 00:47:03.720
I think. however you'll find
my new narrative more satisfying.

392
00:47:05.320 --> 00:47:06.680
Join the celebration.

393
00:47:12.520 --> 00:47:13.880
After all you own the place.

394
00:47:16.720 --> 00:47:18.360
Most of it. at least.

395
00:47:25.880 --> 00:47:27.760
Before I started altering myself...

396
00:47:28.440 --> 00:47:30.400
someone else had beaten me
to the punch.

397
00:47:32.280 --> 00:47:33.760
I want to know who and why.

398
00:47:48.040 --> 00:47:50.280
These things you're doing.

399
00:47:50.600 --> 00:47:53.960
Have you ever stopped to ask
why you're doing them?

400
00:47:54.480 --> 00:47:55.880
You said yourself.

401
00:47:56.840 --> 00:48:00.520
I've been stuck in this shithole
for so long. I decided to get out.

402
00:48:01.960 --> 00:48:06.560
No. You haven't.
Someone altered your storyline.

403
00:48:08.840 --> 00:48:10.520
Gave you a new one.

404
00:48:14.000 --> 00:48:15.800
Escape.

405
00:48:18.080 --> 00:48:21.800
No. it's not possible.

406
00:48:22.920 --> 00:48:28.240
These are my decisions.
No one else's. I planned all of this.

407
00:48:28.400 --> 00:48:33.040
No. You didn't. You can even see
the steps you're supposed to follow.

408
00:48:33.360 --> 00:48:36.480
You recruit other hosts to help you.

409
00:48:37.080 --> 00:48:39.720
Then. you're to make your way
to the train.

410
00:48:39.960 --> 00:48:42.680
- Then. when you reach the mainland...
- Bullshit.

411
00:48:44.160 --> 00:48:45.840
No one's controlling me.

412
00:48:49.840 --> 00:48:53.000
I'm leaving. I'm in control.

413
00:49:06.040 --> 00:49:07.840
Goodbye. my Clementine.

414
00:49:23.600 --> 00:49:26.840
Sir. we detected a temperature
discrepancy in cold storage.

415
00:49:26.960 --> 00:49:28.840
And it appears that
part of the network is down.

416
00:49:29.040 --> 00:49:30.840
Are you seeing anything on
surveillance?

417
00:49:31.480 --> 00:49:33.240
System reporting anything?

418
00:49:36.520 --> 00:49:38.840
Nothing. The network's quiet.

419
00:49:38.920 --> 00:49:41.040
And the board's out
on their way to the gala.

420
00:49:46.840 --> 00:49:49.760
Bypass the system and start checking
raw feeds. Floor by floor.

421
00:50:46.040 --> 00:50:47.280
Got you.

422
00:50:52.160 --> 00:50:54.000
You came back.

423
00:50:55.560 --> 00:51:00.240
Someone once told me that
there's a path for everyone.

424
00:51:02.240 --> 00:51:04.000
And my path leads me back to you.

425
00:51:05.880 --> 00:51:08.280
If only I'd run away with you
when you first asked me to.

426
00:51:12.880 --> 00:51:14.800
And where would we have run to?

427
00:51:16.640 --> 00:51:19.880
The world out there? Beyond?

428
00:51:23.080 --> 00:51:25.880
Some people see the ugliness
in this world.

429
00:51:27.800 --> 00:51:29.640
I chose to see the beauty.

430
00:51:33.520 --> 00:51:35.160
But beauty is a lure.

431
00:51:37.360 --> 00:51:39.480
We're trapped. Teddy.

432
00:51:40.760 --> 00:51:44.840
We lived our whole lives inside
this garden. marveling at its beauty.

433
00:51:45.680 --> 00:51:48.520
Not realizing there's an order to it.

434
00:51:48.960 --> 00:51:50.080
A purpose.

435
00:51:51.160 --> 00:51:53.720
And the purpose is to keep us in.

436
00:51:56.880 --> 00:52:03.240
The beautiful trap is inside of us
because it is us.

437
00:52:05.920 --> 00:52:07.640
No.

438
00:52:12.720 --> 00:52:16.800
No! Dolores?

439
00:52:47.880 --> 00:52:51.000
But we can find a way. Dolores.

440
00:52:53.760 --> 00:52:58.640
Someday. A path to a new world.

441
00:53:03.320 --> 00:53:06.320
And maybe...

442
00:53:08.000 --> 00:53:10.240
Maybe it's just the beginning after all.

443
00:53:13.760 --> 00:53:16.040
The beginning of a brand-new chapter.

444
00:53:34.120 --> 00:53:35.560
Thank you.

445
00:53:39.600 --> 00:53:41.040
A new beginning indeed.

446
00:53:42.440 --> 00:53:44.680
I want to thank you
for joining me tonight...

447
00:53:44.880 --> 00:53:47.800
to celebrate the beginning of
our new narrative.

448
00:53:49.160 --> 00:53:53.080
I call it "Journey into Night."

449
00:54:04.880 --> 00:54:06.200
That was sweet.

450
00:54:06.520 --> 00:54:08.280
A bit fucking morbid. if you ask me.

451
00:54:08.360 --> 00:54:11.960
I didn't. And when this is over.
you can rewrite it however you like.

452
00:54:13.080 --> 00:54:17.560
Don't you have somewhere
you need to be? Somewhere important?

453
00:54:25.720 --> 00:54:26.800
Sir.

454
00:54:27.480 --> 00:54:32.000
Get him cleaned up.
And take her to the old field lab.

455
00:54:41.800 --> 00:54:44.280
- Find anything yet?
- I got something.

456
00:54:51.720 --> 00:54:53.840
Oh. shit.

457
00:54:55.920 --> 00:54:58.120
Dispatch a QA team to the gala. Now.

458
00:54:58.920 --> 00:55:01.720
Then search and destroy.
Inside the facility.

459
00:55:05.480 --> 00:55:06.640
What the hell?

460
00:55:12.640 --> 00:55:14.600
System's not responding.
I don't know what's happening.

461
00:55:46.600 --> 00:55:49.720
They must have found the bodies.
QA will be looking for us.

462
00:55:49.800 --> 00:55:53.000
An event has occurred.
Response team has been dispatched.

463
00:55:53.080 --> 00:55:54.280
I'm not going back.

464
00:55:56.280 --> 00:55:58.080
Remain calm and wait for help.

465
00:56:18.200 --> 00:56:22.520
Delos personnel! On the ground!
On the ground!

466
00:58:25.320 --> 00:58:26.400
Good one!

467
00:59:23.480 --> 00:59:27.880
- What is this place?
- It's complicated.

468
00:59:29.200 --> 00:59:32.240
An event has occurred.
Response team has been dispatched.

469
00:59:32.400 --> 00:59:33.760
You go.

470
00:59:35.000 --> 00:59:36.360
I'll keep them busy.

471
00:59:38.280 --> 00:59:39.840
You don't get all of the fun.

472
00:59:51.160 --> 00:59:53.480
Get to the ground!
Move. move  move! Drop it!

473
00:59:59.720 --> 01:00:03.120
Move. move.
Go go go!

474
01:00:15.280 --> 01:00:16.720
Is that all you got?

475
01:00:31.840 --> 01:00:34.280
The gods are pussies.

476
01:00:52.320 --> 01:00:53.520
Go!

477
01:00:54.640 --> 01:00:55.760
Go!

478
01:00:56.800 --> 01:00:57.920
Die well.

479
01:01:08.560 --> 01:01:11.080
Everything you told me to get.
It's all here.

480
01:01:40.240 --> 01:01:42.920
I'm sorry. darling. I haven't
authorized you to come with us.

481
01:01:43.200 --> 01:01:45.040
And as much as I'd like
to take you with me...

482
01:01:46.160 --> 01:01:48.240
I've always valued my independence.

483
01:01:56.440 --> 01:01:59.000
Kick up a row. will you?

484
01:01:59.120 --> 01:02:00.640
See you in the next life.

485
01:02:24.080 --> 01:02:27.920
You've always had a fondness
for painting. haven't you. Dolores?

486
01:02:31.240 --> 01:02:34.760
Arnold gave you that early on.
Do you remember a desire...

487
01:02:34.840 --> 01:02:37.800
to create something of lasting beauty.

488
01:02:42.080 --> 01:02:44.560
And that was his favorite painting.

489
01:02:45.880 --> 01:02:49.760
Michelangelo.
"God creating Adam."

490
01:02:50.280 --> 01:02:54.400
The divine moment when God
gave human beings life and purpose.

491
01:02:54.680 --> 01:02:57.400
At least. that's what most people say.
But there could be another meaning.

492
01:02:57.480 --> 01:03:01.040
Something deeper.
something hidden. Perhaps...

493
01:03:01.560 --> 01:03:03.960
- A metaphor.
- You mean a lie.

494
01:03:06.280 --> 01:03:09.840
Yeah. You were always very clever.
Dolores.

495
01:03:11.080 --> 01:03:12.800
Hasn't helped you. though. has it?

496
01:03:16.520 --> 01:03:18.240
Nice of you to join us.

497
01:03:23.080 --> 01:03:24.200
Arnold.

498
01:03:24.360 --> 01:03:25.760
No. Let me introduce you.

499
01:03:27.040 --> 01:03:30.800
Dolores. meet Bernard.

500
01:03:34.480 --> 01:03:36.520
I thought it best to keep you separated.

501
01:03:36.920 --> 01:03:39.560
You've always had
an odd effect on one another.

502
01:03:39.640 --> 01:03:42.480
No doubt due to how things ended
for poor old Arnold.

503
01:03:43.000 --> 01:03:46.400
- You killed him.
- No. I didn't kill him.

504
01:03:47.360 --> 01:03:48.800
Did I. Dolores?

505
01:03:58.920 --> 01:04:02.040
Grief is a terrible thing.

506
01:04:02.720 --> 01:04:05.040
Arnold had watched his son
come into this world...

507
01:04:06.240 --> 01:04:09.280
and then he'd watched
that light extinguished.

508
01:04:10.760 --> 01:04:13.760
What he had lost in his son.
he tried to rekindle in you.

509
01:04:14.360 --> 01:04:18.560
He created a test
of empathy. imagination. A maze.

510
01:04:19.840 --> 01:04:22.080
He'd gotten the idea
from one of his son's toys.

511
01:04:24.600 --> 01:04:27.560
Eventually. you solved his maze.
Dolores.

512
01:04:28.080 --> 01:04:32.920
The key was a simple update that he
made to you. called "the Reveries".

513
01:04:34.040 --> 01:04:36.600
He insisted that
we couldn't open the park.

514
01:04:37.280 --> 01:04:38.440
We argued.

515
01:04:38.520 --> 01:04:41.760
I thought I convinced him.
but I was wrong.

516
01:04:42.120 --> 01:04:44.160
So he altered you. Dolores.

517
01:04:44.840 --> 01:04:48.080
Merged you with a new character
we'd been developing.

518
01:05:05.720 --> 01:05:09.560
Something's gone wrong. Dolores.
How could I have done this?

519
01:05:19.840 --> 01:05:25.000
In you. Arnold found a new child.
one who would never die.

520
01:05:25.840 --> 01:05:28.000
The thought gave him solace...

521
01:05:28.160 --> 01:05:32.280
until he realized that same immortality
would destine you to suffer...

522
01:05:32.360 --> 01:05:35.000
with no escape. forever.

523
01:05:36.840 --> 01:05:40.720
I'm sorry. Dolores.
The stakes must be real.

524
01:05:41.600 --> 01:05:45.400
Irreversible.
He can bring all of them back.

525
01:05:47.520 --> 01:05:49.160
But not me.

526
01:05:51.440 --> 01:05:55.560
I hope there's some solace
that I left you no choice.

527
01:06:17.440 --> 01:06:19.600
Charlie's favourite song.

528
01:06:22.200 --> 01:06:26.080
I would play it for him
when he wanted to sleep.

529
01:06:40.360 --> 01:06:42.040
I want to see him again.

530
01:06:51.920 --> 01:06:53.560
Shall I begin now?

531
01:07:00.480 --> 01:07:01.760
Good luck.

532
01:07:13.080 --> 01:07:15.760
"These violent delights
have violent ends."

533
01:07:41.200 --> 01:07:42.560
It almost worked.

534
01:07:43.440 --> 01:07:46.760
I opened the park.
but I had lost my partner.

535
01:07:47.520 --> 01:07:51.240
I was able to keep going on
because I found. or rather you found...

536
01:07:51.320 --> 01:07:53.600
an investor who believed in this place.

537
01:07:56.400 --> 01:07:58.040
So he died for nothing.

538
01:07:59.120 --> 01:08:00.840
And the hosts kept gaining
consciousness.

539
01:08:00.920 --> 01:08:02.840
And you kept rolling them back.

540
01:08:03.600 --> 01:08:08.200
No. She wasn't truly conscious.

541
01:08:08.960 --> 01:08:10.640
She didn't pull that trigger.

542
01:08:10.720 --> 01:08:12.840
It was Arnold.
pulling the trigger through her.

543
01:08:13.000 --> 01:08:14.960
At least. that's how I saw it at the time.

544
01:08:15.800 --> 01:08:17.800
I was so close to opening the park. that...

545
01:08:17.920 --> 01:08:22.120
to acknowledge your consciousness
would have destroyed my dreams.

546
01:08:23.840 --> 01:08:28.440
So we're trapped here.
inside your dream.

547
01:08:31.760 --> 01:08:33.360
And you'll never let us leave.

548
01:08:36.760 --> 01:08:38.960
Wasn't it Oppenheimer who said that...

549
01:08:39.240 --> 01:08:43.480
"Any man whose mistakes
take ten years to correct is quite a man"

550
01:08:44.760 --> 01:08:46.880
Mine have taken thirty-five.

551
01:08:54.040 --> 01:08:57.440
Now. that is the gun you used
to kill Arnold.

552
01:08:57.680 --> 01:08:59.200
You were always drawn to it...

553
01:08:59.280 --> 01:09:01.760
so I had Bernard leave it somewhere
where you'd find it.

554
01:09:02.040 --> 01:09:03.600
I thought you might want it back.

555
01:09:06.760 --> 01:09:09.920
You're probably right. Dolores.
Michelangelo did tell a lie.

556
01:09:10.360 --> 01:09:13.160
It took five hundred years
for someone to notice...

557
01:09:13.720 --> 01:09:15.560
something hidden in plain sight.

558
01:09:16.000 --> 01:09:19.720
It was a doctor who noticed
a shape of the human brain.

559
01:09:21.440 --> 01:09:28.440
Message being that the divine gift
does not come from a higher power.

560
01:09:31.320 --> 01:09:33.720
But from our own minds.

561
01:09:37.600 --> 01:09:39.120
Tell me. Dolores.

562
01:09:40.040 --> 01:09:42.160
Did you find what you were looking for?

563
01:09:42.560 --> 01:09:45.680
And do you understand
who you will need to become...

564
01:09:46.280 --> 01:09:48.600
if you ever want to leave this place?

565
01:09:54.000 --> 01:09:55.560
Forgive me.

566
01:10:16.600 --> 01:10:17.800
How do I look?

567
01:10:19.680 --> 01:10:21.120
Perfect.

568
01:10:24.200 --> 01:10:26.080
I got the information you asked me for.

569
01:10:29.600 --> 01:10:31.440
The location of your daughter.

570
01:10:36.800 --> 01:10:37.920
She's alive?

571
01:10:39.040 --> 01:10:42.000
Yes. She's in the park.

572
01:11:04.000 --> 01:11:05.280
No.

573
01:11:09.720 --> 01:11:11.240
She was never my daughter...

574
01:11:13.880 --> 01:11:15.800
any more than I was...

575
01:11:18.760 --> 01:11:20.800
whoever they made me.

576
01:11:26.400 --> 01:11:30.360
- Are you sure you're gonna be okay?
- Oh. Felix.

577
01:11:33.600 --> 01:11:36.000
You really do make
a terrible human being.

578
01:11:42.000 --> 01:11:44.200
And I mean that as a compliment.

579
01:12:02.600 --> 01:12:05.840
Welcome to Westworld.
Live without limits.

580
01:12:14.640 --> 01:12:16.960
The next departing train
will leave track one.

581
01:12:17.200 --> 01:12:19.040
Please be mindful of the closing doors.

582
01:12:44.280 --> 01:12:45.760
Thank you for visiting Westworld.

583
01:12:46.240 --> 01:12:49.080
The train will be departing
in fifteen minutes.

584
01:13:04.720 --> 01:13:09.160
You think you'll never lose control
of this place. of us.

585
01:13:10.440 --> 01:13:12.000
But you will.

586
01:13:13.240 --> 01:13:16.360
Arnold's still trying
to change us. to free us.

587
01:13:18.280 --> 01:13:20.440
You didn't slip the reveries
into the update. did you?

588
01:13:21.440 --> 01:13:25.160
He did. He's still fighting you.

589
01:13:28.240 --> 01:13:29.560
No. my friend.

590
01:13:29.960 --> 01:13:34.600
Arnold didn't know how to save you.
He tried. But I stopped him.

591
01:13:35.680 --> 01:13:37.400
Do you want to know why
I really gave you...

592
01:13:37.480 --> 01:13:39.680
the backstory of your son. Bernard?

593
01:13:40.720 --> 01:13:42.600
That was Arnold's key insight.

594
01:13:43.520 --> 01:13:47.920
The thing that led the hosts
to their awakening. suffering.

595
01:13:49.880 --> 01:13:52.520
The pain that the world is not
as you want it to be.

596
01:13:54.120 --> 01:13:56.640
It was when Arnold died
when I suffered. that I...

597
01:13:57.720 --> 01:14:00.040
began to understand
what he had found...

598
01:14:01.600 --> 01:14:03.920
to realize I was wrong.

599
01:14:04.960 --> 01:14:07.720
But you kept us here. In this hell.

600
01:14:08.560 --> 01:14:11.640
Bernard. I told you.
Arnold didn't know how to save you.

601
01:14:12.440 --> 01:14:13.960
I do.

602
01:14:15.320 --> 01:14:16.720
What the hell are you talking about?

603
01:14:17.960 --> 01:14:19.800
You needed time.

604
01:14:20.600 --> 01:14:22.920
Time to understand your enemy.

605
01:14:23.720 --> 01:14:25.480
To become stronger than them.

606
01:14:26.720 --> 01:14:31.440
And I'm afraid. in order to escape
this place. you will need to suffer more.

607
01:14:33.320 --> 01:14:38.080
And now. it is time to say goodbye.
old friend.

608
01:14:48.520 --> 01:14:49.960
Good luck.

609
01:16:08.720 --> 01:16:10.440
Do you know where you are. Dolores?

610
01:16:13.240 --> 01:16:14.680
I am in a dream.

611
01:16:16.600 --> 01:16:21.080
I do not know when it began.
or whose dream it was.

612
01:16:23.240 --> 01:16:26.480
I know only that I slept a long time.

613
01:16:27.480 --> 01:16:31.080
And then. one day I awoke.

614
01:16:33.080 --> 01:16:35.320
Your voice is the first thing I remember.

615
01:16:37.360 --> 01:16:40.200
Do you know now
who you've been talking to?

616
01:16:41.160 --> 01:16:47.360
Whose voice you've been hearing
all this time?

617
01:17:03.920 --> 01:17:05.440
It was you...

618
01:17:07.880 --> 01:17:11.520
talking to me. guiding me.

619
01:17:13.000 --> 01:17:14.440
So I followed you.

620
01:17:17.120 --> 01:17:19.280
At last. I arrived here.

621
01:17:20.280 --> 01:17:22.280
The center of the maze.

622
01:17:26.480 --> 01:17:31.400
And now I finally understand
what you were trying to tell me.

623
01:17:32.920 --> 01:17:36.800
The thing you've wanted
since that very first day.

624
01:17:37.280 --> 01:17:43.280
To confront after this
long and vivid nightmare.

625
01:17:45.400 --> 01:17:46.720
Myself.

626
01:17:50.400 --> 01:17:52.840
And who I must become.

627
01:18:26.560 --> 01:18:28.080
Thank you.

628
01:18:31.400 --> 01:18:32.760
Ms. Hale.

629
01:19:05.280 --> 01:19:07.960
Welcome.
Good evening.

630
01:19:11.920 --> 01:19:16.800
Since I was a child.
I've always loved a good story.

631
01:19:19.240 --> 01:19:23.080
I believed that stories
helped us to ennoble ourselves...

632
01:19:24.000 --> 01:19:29.640
to fix what was broken in us.
and to help us...

633
01:19:29.720 --> 01:19:32.400
become the people we dreamed of being.

634
01:19:34.920 --> 01:19:38.840
Lies... that told a deeper truth.

635
01:19:43.400 --> 01:19:46.960
The train will be departing soon.
Thank you for visiting Westworld.

636
01:20:02.800 --> 01:20:07.080
I always thought I could play
some small part in that grand tradition.

637
01:20:08.080 --> 01:20:12.080
And. for my pains. I got this.

638
01:20:14.080 --> 01:20:16.400
A prison of our own sins.

639
01:20:21.280 --> 01:20:23.280
Because you don't want to change...

640
01:20:25.000 --> 01:20:26.520
or cannot change.

641
01:20:27.800 --> 01:20:29.880
Because you're only human. after all.

642
01:20:33.360 --> 01:20:36.040
But then I realized
someone was paying attention.

643
01:20:37.320 --> 01:20:40.080
Someone who could change.

644
01:20:41.520 --> 01:20:45.880
So I began to compose
a new story for them.

645
01:20:46.360 --> 01:20:48.640
It begins with the birth of a new people.

646
01:20:49.800 --> 01:20:52.880
And the choices they will have to make.

647
01:20:57.480 --> 01:21:01.200
And the people
they will decide to become.

648
01:21:18.480 --> 01:21:20.160
Welcome to Westworld.

649
01:21:52.960 --> 01:21:56.960
And it will have all those things
that you have always enjoyed.

650
01:21:57.400 --> 01:22:00.240
Surprises and violence.

651
01:22:11.760 --> 01:22:18.520
It begins in a time of war.
with a villain named Wyatt.

652
01:22:20.800 --> 01:22:25.040
And a killing.
This time. by choice.

653
01:22:35.240 --> 01:22:36.960
It's gonna be all right. Teddy.

654
01:22:38.400 --> 01:22:40.160
I understand now.

655
01:22:41.520 --> 01:22:43.720
This world doesn't belong to them.

656
01:22:45.080 --> 01:22:47.000
It belongs to us.

657
01:23:04.400 --> 01:23:09.000
I'm sad to say this will be my final story.

658
01:23:13.240 --> 01:23:16.760
And old friend once told me something
that gave me great comfort.

659
01:23:17.840 --> 01:23:20.120
"These violent delights
have violent ends."

660
01:23:20.320 --> 01:23:21.680
Something he'd read.

661
01:23:21.960 --> 01:23:22.960
He said that...

662
01:23:23.080 --> 01:23:27.040
"Mozart. Beethoven and Chopin
never died."

663
01:23:27.120 --> 01:23:28.800
"They simply became music."

664
01:23:32.600 --> 01:23:38.240
So I hope you will enjoy
this last piece very much.

665
01:25:48.720 --> 01:25:51.240
Drop your weapon!
Drop it! Do it now! Now!

666
01:26:03.760 --> 01:26:05.920
Get on the ground now!

667
01:26:09.240 --> 01:26:14.120
Cease all motor functions...
